Police are investigating a case of murder after a 22-year-old Port Elizabeth man was shot on Saturday. Police spokeswoman Captain Sandra Janse van Rensburg said Daniel Vaaltyn had died on the way to hospital after the shooting in Kumasi Street, Jacksonville, shortly before 7am. The motive for the shooting was still unknown, she said. Vaaltyn was relatively well known in his community, where he ran errands and did odd jobs. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share